Miscellaneous Highlights: Malaysia and Kuwait advanced to the regional final of T20 World Cup 2026 qualification.
Rain and net run rate affected the match between Hong Kong, China against Kuwait.
Syed Aziz was the star for Malaysia, making 216 runs at a strike rate of 174.
Usman Patel, Clinto Anto, and Ravija Sandaruwan all finished in the top-five run getters for Kuwait.
Yasin Patel took 15 wickets at an economy of 4.85, and Shiraz Khan took eight wickets at an economy of 4.75 for Kuwait.
Hong Kong finished third in the group, but will be cursing the weather gods after their final match ended in a no result.
Singapore finished fourth with four wins, including an upset over Kuwait.
Maldives and Myanmar managed to bat all of their 20 overs in each of their encounters with the stronger group members.
